article.headline: Northern Arizona 83, Montana 80
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Kelly Golob scored 22 points and Steven Sir added 20 as Northern Arizona used a second-half rally to beat Montana 83-80 in a Big Sky Conference game Thursday night. The Lumberjacks (13-6, 5-0 Big Sky) trailed 45-32 at halftime as Montana (13-3, 3-1) made 10 3-pointers in 13 attempts and shot 64 percent from the field overall. Northern Arizona chipped away at the deficit and went ahead to stay with 8:29 remaining on an 18-foot jumper by Ruben Boykin Jr. Boykin finished with 12 points while Ryan McCurdy added 10. Kevin Criswell had 24 points for the Grizzlies while Matt Dlouhy scored 14, Andrew Strait 13 and Bryan Ellis and Jordan Hasquet 10 each.
